Sombre mood engulfs Chemoe where the 30-year-old constable had served for more than two years.Tension high in the area with reports indicating that residents are fleeing their homes for fear of more attacks by criminals. In April last year, five police officers survived a tragic accident that saw seven of their colleagues drown in a raging Kagir River in Baringo North.
The 12 officers attached to the Anti-Stock Theft Unit based in banditry-prone Chemoe at the border of Baringo North and Tiaty sub-counties in Baringo County, were heading back to their camp from a security meeting at the county headquarters in Kabarnet when they got stuck in a seasonal river on April 29 at 8pm prompting them to disembark to push it out.



