Constable Patrick King’ori was among the lucky ones. The others were Joseph Omboye, Andrew Menisa, Cliff Nyakeniga and Bernard Sigei.
But on Thursday, Patrick King’ori’s luck ran out when he was shot by bandits while on patrol.
According to police reports, Mr King’ori and nine of his colleagues were fetching firewood on the way back to their station from patrol when they were attacked by bandits. He was shot in the stomach while trying to flee from the attackers.
Baringo North Sub-County Police Commander Fredrick Odinga said the injured officer was rushed to Marigat Sub-County Hospital but healthcare workers were on strike so he was transferred to Nakuru but died on the way.
A sombre mood engulfed the Chemoe where the 30-year-old constable had served for more than two years.
“It is sad that we lost him in the hands of armed criminals. The officer would have survived but he couldn’t find medical help,” said County Police Commander Robinson Ndiwa.



